HEADWORD: Levesel
<hw>Lev"e*sel</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧v"⟦esl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[AS. <ets>le⟦aacute⟧f</ets> a leaf + <ets>s⟦ae⟧l</ets>,
<ets>sel</ets>, a room, a hall.]</ety> <def>A leafy shelter; a place
covered with foliage.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behind the mill, under a <qex>levesel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
